Title: Detecting Semantic Interference in Parallel Changes: An Exploratory Case Study
Purpose: detect semantic interference between parallel changes
UseOF-SZZ:
We similar identify changes, but
differ in how we identify fault-inducing changes. Our

mining version histories and bug databases.
Summary:
empirical study on the semantic
interference detection algorithm in the context of a
large industrial project.
